dcterms:description: The proposed image compression framework is trained on Open Images Dataset V5, which contains 9 million images belonging to 600 boxable categories. The images in this dataset are diverse and contain complex scenes with 8 objects per image on average.
dcterms:title: Open Images Dataset V5

dcterms:description: The Kodak dataset comprises 25 landscape or portrait RGB images of size 768 Ã— 512 pixels. It is widely used in image compression tasks and serves as a generic benchmark data collection.
dcterms:title: Kodak Dataset

dcterms:description: The ImageNet 2012 classification dataset consists of images belonging to 1000 classes. It is split into three sets: training (1.3M images), validation (50K images), and testing (100K images with held-out class labels).
dcterms:title: ImageNet Dataset

dcterms:description: The TIMIT dataset contains a total of 6300 sentences spoken by 630 speakers from 8 major dialect regions of the United States at a sample rate of 16 kHz.
dcterms:title: TIMIT Dataset
